The defendant Jan A Doenier was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Felony, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Jan A Doenier in court with attorney Sydne French.  Timothy Suha appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant enters a plea of no contest to Count 1,  Court finds defendant guilty.  Cases 14CM570, 14CM764 and 14FO181 dismissed and read in to this matter and to 14CF452.

Court orders the following.
- Sentence withheld.  Credit for 35 days if revoked.
- 3 years Probation.  Court would appove Early Termination of Probation after 2 years if defendant is able to maintain absolute sobriety.
- Court costs of $268.00; cash bail to be applied.
- DNA Surcharge of $250.00; cash bail to be applied.
- Cash bail to be applied to Court costs and DNA surcharge in this matter and to fine in 14TR5473.  Any remaining cash bail to be refunded to poster.
- Conditions of Probation:  Maintain absolute sobriety/Random UAs.  No use or possession of alcohol/drug paraphernalia/drugs without a valid prescription.  Valid prescriptions to be taken in the manner they were prescribed and must be verified to the Agent.  Follow through with Mental Health treatment/counseling.  Defendant not to drive a motor vehicle without a valid license and IID.  Contact with estranged husband and daughter as directed by Courts with competent jurisdiction or as otherwise approved by Agent.  Attend a minimum of 2 self help meetings per week.
CONDITION TIME: 60 days - NON WORKING HOURS WITH STANDARD RELEASE CONDITIONS - STAYED for use by Agent.
